Here's what each part of the format (e.g., YYYY) represents:

YYYY : Year (4 digits) - Example: 2023

YY : Year (2 digits) - Example: 23

MMMM : Month (full name) - Example: September

MMM : Month (short name) - Example: Sep

MM : Month (2 digits) - Example: 09

DDDD : Day (full name) - Example: Sunday

DDD : Day (short name) - Example: Sun

HH : Hour (2 digits) - Example: 11

mm : Minute (2 digits) - Example: 23

ss : Second (2 digits) - Example: 58
